'''Level 904''' is the 905<sup>th</sup> level of [[The Backrooms]] and a very pleasant level.
==<span style="font-family:Work Sans">Description</span>==
{{Blurquote|image=FallenSkies.png|person=Connor D.|quote-text=I sat down and admired the amazing auroras..}}
'''Level 904''' is widely known as one of the most peaceful known levels. Many wanderers use it as a recovery point before continuing exploration. No geometrical changes, instability, or hostile events have ever been recorded.
{{Blurimage|file=Aurora borealis.jpg|caption='''Aurora Borealis''' found on '''Level 904'''.|hovertext=What an amazing view..}}
{{Blurimage|file=FallenSkies.png|caption=The Auroras found on '''Level 904'''.|hovertext=Welcome to '''Iceland'''!}}
{{Blurimage|file=Multicolored northern lights aurora borealison canadian.jpg|caption=One of the biggest auroras you can find in '''Level 904'''.|hovertext=Reminds me of Level 2000: "Ursa Major"..}}
{{Blurimage|file=Luna major.png|caption=Blue '''Aurora Borealis''' found on '''Level 904'''.|hovertext=shibby (running out of ideas for this lol)}}
'''Level 904''', also known as "Fallen Skies" is a very large, open area with a calm, flat snowy landscape and a sky full of permanent auroral formations. The ground has a smooth, matte surface that resembles polished stone or frozen glass, and it feels cool to the touch but not cold. Even though you can't see any texture, it has great grip and stability.


The sky is what makes the level unique. Big curtains of auroras run slowly from horizon to horizon. They are different shades of green, cyan, violet, and soft gold. Unlike auroras seen in [[The Frontrooms|reality]], these lights look closer, as if the sky had fallen, which is how the level got its name. There is no sun, moon, or stars visible because the auroras give off a soft glow that is the same brightness as dusk. You can feel that the ground is cool, but not cold. Its smooth, matte surface looks like stone or frozen glass.


There are no weather events, wind, or temperature changes. The environment remains completely stuck and peaceful, regardless of how long a wanderer remains. Even after decades, centuries, milleniums, it will stay completely still. Despite the complete lack of motion or movement, the level does not feel fake or unstable. Instead, it conveys a sense of gentle permanence, as if it existed without urgency or decay. The air is clear and neutral, with no discernible odor or discomfort when inhaled for extended periods of time.


Lighting conditions never change. Shadows are soft and diffuse, with no obvious light source casting them. Objects brought into the level, such as equipment, supplies, or personal items, are unaffected by the environment and show no signs of degrading with time. Electronic devices function normally, but signals like radio transmissions do not reach any known frequency or external receiver.


People who stay in '''Level 904''' for a long time often have a different sense of time. Wanderers often sreport that they feel like only minutes have passed when in reality hours or days have passed. However, no one has actually measured this distortion of time. There are mostly positive psychological effects, such as less stress, clearer thinking, and a strong sense of calmness. There have been no reports of paranoia, hallucinations, or memory loss linked to this level.

Just sit down and admire the auroras surronding you.
{{Blurimage|file=904.png|caption=So beautiful..|hovertext=Crazy? I Was Crazy Once. They Locked Me In A Room. A Rubber Room. A Rubber Room With Rats. And Rats Make Me Crazy.}}
===Environment Properties===
*Like in [[The Frontrooms]], gravity functions normally in '''Level 904'''. The sky has no end or ceiling, yet feels enclosed and protective rather than infinite.

*Sound is heavily soft; footsteps make little to no noise.

*Looking at the auroras often causes feelings of calm, nostalgia, or emotional sadness.

*Time may feel distorted, though no actual anomalies have been recorded.
Despite the surreal visuals, '''Level 904 shows no signs of danger'''.
==<span style="font-family:Work Sans">Entities</span>==
===<span style="font-family:Work Sans">There are '''no entities in Level 904'''.===
There are no records of any entities that are hostile, neutral, or passive. Even common Backrooms phenomena, like hallucinations, mimicry, or threats to the environment, do not exist. The only living things here are you and the auroras.
==<span style="font-family:Work Sans">Colonies & Outposts</span>==
===<span style="font-family:Work Sans">...===
There are no colonies or outposts in '''Level 904'''. You can just stay and lie on the ground, admiring the amazing auroras.




...




Maybe, there could be one, somewhere..




===<span style="font-family:Work Sans">The Aurora Watchers===
<s>What is assumed to be a community of wanderers make refuge in the woods of '''Level 904'''. Attempts to reach beyond the forest of '''Level 904''' have been made, but have yielded no results. Fifteen wanderers are estimated to live here. Communication is difficult, but not impossible. They appear to have a simple system of stomps, where:</s>
*<s>One stomp = Yes</s>
*<s>Two stomps = No</s>
*<s>Three stomps = Hello/Goodbye</s>

'''Update:''' ''As of March 29th, 2020, the community known as "Aurora Watchers" has been deemed eradicated.''
==<span style="font-family:Work Sans">Entrances & Exits</span>==
===<span style="font-family:Work Sans">Entrances</span>===
*'''Level 904''' can be entered by falling asleep while staring at artificial lighting (such as fluorescent or LED lights) in other '''Class 0''' or '''Class 1''' levels.

*Noclip through reflective surfaces in bright, empty areas in [[The Backrooms]] to send you to '''Level 904'''.

*'''Level 904''' can be rarely accessed from other aurora-like or sky-dominated levels.

===<span style="font-family:Work Sans">Exits</span>===
*Staring directly into the auroras for a few days may send you into another safe '''Class 0''' level.

*Lying down and falling asleep on the surface has been reported to return wanderers to a familiar Backrooms location they previously visited.

*Some explorers say they left on their own after long stays, with no clear reason.
